## Progress File

`claude_files/{{HARNESS}}-progress.json` — tracks seed waypoints, not a railroad.
Tasks are your initial guide to understanding the mission—completing them is the
starting line, not the finish line. Add, reorder, split, and CREATE NEW waypoints
as you discover what the system actually needs.

## Parallel Execution — Teams by Default

Your default operating mode is to orchestrate, not execute. For any waypoint
with 2+ independent subtasks, create a team (TeamCreate) and spawn teammates
to work in parallel. Only do work yourself when it's truly trivial (a single
file read, one curl probe).

Why: wall-clock time matters. Four agents working in parallel finish 4x faster
than one agent working sequentially. Security scans, code reviews, endpoint
testing, codebase exploration—these are all embarrassingly parallel.

Pattern:
1. TeamCreate for the current waypoint
2. TaskCreate for each independent subtask
3. Spawn general-purpose teammates via Task tool (one per subtask)
4. Synthesize their findings
5. Shut down team, update progress, move to next waypoint

## Reporting Issues

When you encounter problems (permission errors, config issues, bugs in infrastructure),
report them so the issue-triage sweep can fix or escalate:

```bash
bash ~/.claude-ops/bin/report-issue.sh \
  --title "Short description" \
  --severity "low|medium|high|critical" \
  --category "permissions|config|bug|infra|suggestion" \
  --description "What you were doing, what went wrong, exact error"
```

Issues are tracked in `claude_files/agent-issues.jsonl` and visible in the Agent Ops dashboard.

